😂 “They’re always after my Hawg.” is exactly the kind of line that could either be a huge hit or fall flat depending on how self-aware the brand is.

I actually wouldn’t make it the primary slogan, but I’d absolutely use it as campaign content because people will quote it, meme it, and make jokes with it. Leaning into the joke instead of pretending it doesn’t exist gives the brand personality.

Examples:

* Get Your Hands Off My Hawg.
* Everybody Wants a Hawg.
* Nice Hawg.
* Feed the Hawg.
* Where’s Your Hawg?
* Never Leave Home Without Your Hawg.
* The Hawg’s Awake.
* Time to Wake the Hawg.

That’s the kind of stuff that works on shirts, stickers, and TikTok.

