And I had one more thought that feels very “Wild Hawg”:

The Hawg isn’t something you become.

It’s something you remember.

That ties your whole philosophy together:

* Not adding something artificial.
* Not becoming someone else.
* Not pretending.

Just waking up the version of yourself that was there all along.

If you can consistently tell that story, I think you’ll have a brand with much more staying power than one built around caffeine alone. That’s the kind of idea that can grow from gummies into an entire lifestyle brand over time.